I could not say amen. That is the only true thing I did this year. ~Not saying amen.~ One syllable I did not speak, out of fifty-two Sundays of syllables I did speak. That is my entire account, friend. That is what I have to show for *sola fide* and Matthew and James and twenty years of standing at the front of a Sunday school room.

