I taught the Reformation. I taught Luther throwing the inkpot. I taught the ninety-five theses nailed to the door. I taught *the just shall live by faith* and I taught it like a man telling a war story about a war he did not fight in. And then the indulgence letter came to my own church and I put it on the roof and I sat under it.

*He looks up at you. His eyes are wet but he is looking straight.*

